    "message_1": "A company produces 20,000 units of a product in a month, and they want to forecast the demand for the next 6 months using the historical data. The demand data of the last 12 months is given below. Find the forecasted demand for the next six months using a 3-month moving average.\n\nMonth (Last 12 months) - Demand\n1 - 18,000\n2 - 22,000\n3 - 24,000\n4 - 20,000\n5 - 16,000\n6 - 19,000\n7 - 21,000\n8 - 25,000\n9 - 27,000\n10 - 23,000\n11 - 19,000\n12 - 20,000",
    "message_2": "To calculate the 3-month moving average, we will take the average of the demand for every three consecutive months. We will then use this method to forecast the demand for the next six months.\n\nMonth (Last 12 months) - Demand - 3-Month Moving Average\n1 - 18,000\n2 - 22,000\n3 - 24,000 - (18,000 + 22,000 + 24,000) / 3 = 21,333\n4 - 20,000 - (22,000 + 24,000 + 20,000) / 3 = 22,000\n5 - 16,000 - (24,000 + 20,000 + 16,000) / 3 = 20,000\n6 - 19,000 - (20,000 + 16,000 + 19,000) / 3 = 18,333\n7 - 21,000 - (16,000 + 19,000 + 21,000) / 3 = 18,667\n8 - 25,000 - (19,000 + 21,000 + 25,000) / 3 = 21,667\n9 - 27,000 - (21,000 + 25,000 + 27,000) / 3 = 24,333\n10 - 23,000 - (25,000 + 27,000 + 23,000) / 3 = 25,000\n11 - 19,000 - (27,000 + 23,000 + 19,000) / 3 = 23,000\n12 - 20,000 - (23,000 + 19,000 + 20,000) / 3 = 20,667\n\nNow, we will use the 3-month moving average to forecast the demand for the next six months:\n\nMonth (Forecast) - 3-Month Moving Average\n13 - (19,000 + 20,000 + 23,000) / 3 = 20,667\n14 - (20,000 + 23,000 + 20,667) / 3 = 21,222\n15 - (23,000 + 20,667 + 21,222) / 3 = 21,630\n16 - (20,667 + 21,222 + 21,630) / 3 = 21,173\n17 - (21,222 + 21,630 + 21,173) / 3 = 21,342\n18 - (21,630 + 21,173 + 21,342) / 3 = 21,382\n\nThe forecasted demand for the next six months using a 3-month moving average is:\n\nMonth 13: 20,667 units\nMonth 14: 21,222 units\nMonth 15: 21,630 units\nMonth 16: 21,173 units\nMonth 17: 21,342 units\nMonth 18: 21,382 units"
